        "timestamp": 1700472253
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Currently the game feels too focussed on apply and exact tactics. By the time one gets to the third world, it gets redundant. I was hoping that at least after the second world, there could be an interlude where some of the proofs are repeated, but with more powerful tactics (tauto, left, right, and ext come to mind), as well as cleaner ways to write proofs for multiple cases (i.e. case, cdot, | notation)</p>",
        "id": 403135690,
        "sender_full_name": "Shreyas Srinivas",
        "timestamp": 1700474893
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>On the one hand, repeating proofs with more powerful tactics after they have been done with simpler tactics helps pedagogically. On the other hand, there is less tedium in further worlds.</p>",
        "id": 403135869,
        "sender_full_name": "Shreyas Srinivas",
        "timestamp": 1700474957
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks for this feedback!  It will be very helpful as I continue to develop the game.</p>",
        "id": 403179921,
        "sender_full_name": "Dan Velleman",
        "timestamp": 1700490021
    }
]